WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.503
Just One Show: The Lost Tapes

2
00:00:04.796 --> 00:00:06.673
GOOD OLD MITCH STRIKES AGAIN

3
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:12.763
I may not be on *Cabeleira ao Trono*.

4
00:00:12.888 --> 00:00:15.474
But I can say that I've discovered a new band.

5
00:00:17.601 --> 00:00:19.520
I had no idea...

6
00:00:19.645 --> 00:00:22.356
that Musculoso had
a volleyball scholarship!

7
00:00:22.481 --> 00:00:23.732
Yeah. cool!

8
00:00:23.857 --> 00:00:26.485
Is that what they took from my story?

9
00:00:26.610 --> 00:00:30.364
It all started
when Starla broke up with me.

10
00:00:30.489 --> 00:00:31.823
I thought I had it all.

11
00:00:31.949 --> 00:00:34.576
The only thing
I was missing was a purpose.

12
00:00:34.701 --> 00:00:37.913
I spent the whole year slacking off
and hanging out at the mall.

13
00:00:38.038 --> 00:00:42.125
I had no idea that everything was going to go wrong.

14
00:00:43.001 --> 00:00:46.547
Time to make a surprise visit
to Starla's workplace.

15
00:00:46.672 --> 00:00:50.050
Hi. where's Starla? She's my girlfriend.

16
00:00:50.842 --> 00:00:52.219
She was his girlfriend.

17
00:00:52.344 --> 00:00:55.222
Huh? Huh? Huh?

18
00:00:56.098 --> 00:00:57.391
MUSCULAR

19
00:00:57.516 --> 00:01:00.561
Starla? Honey! What are you doing?

20
00:01:00.686 --> 00:01:02.854
I have dreams and plans. Mitch!

21
00:01:02.980 --> 00:01:05.857
You're just dragging your feet and stalling!

22
00:01:05.983 --> 00:01:07.859
Sweetheart. I came to visit you.

23
00:01:07.985 --> 00:01:11.446
And play arcade games.

24
00:01:11.572 --> 00:01:14.491
I need to be with someone
whose life is going somewhere.

25
00:01:14.616 --> 00:01:15.951
It's over.

26
00:01:16.076 --> 00:01:18.412
Finish crossing it out. Janine.

27
00:01:20.205 --> 00:01:23.667
Baby. please don't finish crossing it out!

28
00:01:25.168 --> 00:01:26.587
No!

29
00:01:28.880 --> 00:01:31.174
What am I going to do. Big Ghost?

30
00:01:31.300 --> 00:01:32.843
I'm nothing without Starla.

31
00:01:32.968 --> 00:01:35.178
Maybe there's a way
to show her how much she's worth.

32
00:01:35.304 --> 00:01:38.849
I need to find something
I'm good at.

33
00:01:38.974 --> 00:01:42.185
Is that the distinctive sound
of a perfect cut?

34
00:01:43.687 --> 00:01:46.607
How will I know what I'm good at?

35
00:01:48.108 --> 00:01:49.109
Hey. you!

36
00:01:49.234 --> 00:01:51.069
- Hey. kid! Hey!
- What?

37
00:01:51.194 --> 00:01:54.990
My name is Dan Diggs.
I think you have a natural talent for volleyball.

38
00:01:55.115 --> 00:01:57.743
I'm a professional volleyball player.
Or rather. I used to be.

39
00:01:57.868 --> 00:02:00.120
I'm 26 now. and I've been through a lot.

40
00:02:00.245 --> 00:02:03.332
But you.
you'd be a star at beach volleyball.

41
00:02:03.457 --> 00:02:05.125
Beach volleyball?

42
00:02:05.250 --> 00:02:08.545
Please agree to be my partner
in the next tournament.

43
00:02:08.670 --> 00:02:11.340
Yeah. I'm kind of busy trying to
prove something to my ex-girlfriend

44
00:02:11.465 --> 00:02:13.175
that I can amount to something in life.

45
00:02:13.300 --> 00:02:17.012
Unless you think this whole
beach volleyball thing will work.

46
00:02:17.137 --> 00:02:18.764
Yes. I think so.

47
00:02:18.889 --> 00:02:20.766
Then I'll do whatever it takes.

48
00:02:31.693 --> 00:02:33.111
WET AND SALTY HOT DOG

49
00:02:44.665 --> 00:02:46.875
Good job. kid. I knew you could do it.

50
00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:49.961
I feel great.
I'm ready for anything. Right?

51
00:02:50.087 --> 00:02:52.631
Steve. you're so motivated.

52
00:02:52.756 --> 00:02:54.800
Starla. who is that guy?

53
00:02:54.925 --> 00:02:57.052
I just met him at the beach.

54
00:02:57.177 --> 00:03:00.889
He has a degree in business administration.
and owns a house in Tahiti

55
00:03:01.014 --> 00:03:04.393
and he's really good at beach volleyball.

56
00:03:04.518 --> 00:03:05.811
Wow!

57
00:03:05.936 --> 00:03:10.482
It's my longtime rival. Dan Diggs. who
lost so badly in last year's tournament

58
00:03:10.607 --> 00:03:12.734
that the soul left the body?

59
00:03:12.859 --> 00:03:13.860
Steve.

60
00:03:13.985 --> 00:03:16.405
He's also great at taking jabs.

61
00:03:16.530 --> 00:03:18.657
It's time to make this official.

62
00:03:18.782 --> 00:03:20.242
Janine!

63
00:03:23.370 --> 00:03:25.372
STEVE

64
00:03:25.497 --> 00:03:27.082
No!

65
00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:28.625
Hey. kid. how's it going?

66
00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:31.378
Come on. Steve. Let's go.

67
00:03:31.503 --> 00:03:33.422
Of course. my girlfriend.

68
00:03:33.547 --> 00:03:34.631
Starla. no!

69
00:03:34.756 --> 00:03:39.010
You won't win her back by whining.
You'll win her back by winning.

70
00:03:39.136 --> 00:03:40.429
It's time for the tournament.

71
00:03:40.554 --> 00:03:44.015
A totally normal beach volleyball tournament.
I'm ready.

72
00:03:44.141 --> 00:03:46.059
Wait. Didn't I tell you?

73
00:03:46.184 --> 00:03:48.395
It's the Underground Beach Volleyball Tournament.

74
00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:50.480
So. does that mean it's safer?

75
00:03:50.605 --> 00:03:52.691
That means it's more than just dangerous.

76
00:03:52.816 --> 00:03:56.194
It is a constant nightmare
where cosmic horrors thrive.

77
00:03:56.319 --> 00:03:59.406
But if you win.
you'll receive a full scholarship.

78
00:03:59.531 --> 00:04:01.783
If I get a
full scholarship.

79
00:04:01.908 --> 00:04:04.202
It will prove that I'm doing
something with my life

80
00:04:04.327 --> 00:04:05.954
and I'll be able to win Starla back.

81
00:04:06.079 --> 00:04:07.497
Let's do this.

82
00:04:19.801 --> 00:04:23.680
- Hot bone! I've got a hot bone!
- Cool.

83
00:04:25.807 --> 00:04:27.058
A dolphin?

84
00:04:27.184 --> 00:04:29.686
It's not a dolphin. It's Blake.

85
00:04:29.811 --> 00:04:34.900
A little girl genetically modified
to be an absolute beast at volleyball.

86
00:04:35.025 --> 00:04:37.360
What's that on his forehead?

87
00:04:37.486 --> 00:04:41.406
A visor formed
from his own bones.

88
00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:44.743
Don't touch me. you jerk.

89
00:04:44.868 --> 00:04:48.580
Your job is to translate.
and to translate only. Do you understand?

90
00:04:48.705 --> 00:04:49.706
I see.

91
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:51.833
I'm going to register our team.

92
00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:55.921
Look. it's the cadet. Musculoso.

93
00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:58.799
Or rather. that weird tan.

94
00:04:58.924 --> 00:05:00.425
What? No!

95
00:05:01.927 --> 00:05:05.055
I liked your joke.
because it's mean and true.

96
00:05:06.014 --> 00:05:09.976
Muscular. Good luck before the game.
You're going to kill it.

97
00:05:10.101 --> 00:05:13.021
Thanks. Fantasmão.
but they're right. I'm just a rookie.

98
00:05:13.146 --> 00:05:15.440
Do you know what the best part of my day was?

99
00:05:15.565 --> 00:05:18.777
When I went to pick him up at his trailer
and you didn't answer.

100
00:05:18.902 --> 00:05:22.656
Because I knew you had finally
gone out to do something with your life.

101
00:05:22.781 --> 00:05:24.032
Or I've lost track of time again.

102
00:05:24.157 --> 00:05:26.618
Thanks. Fantasmão. You're the real deal.

103
00:05:27.369 --> 00:05:28.370
A real what?

104
00:05:28.495 --> 00:05:31.832
Ladies and gentlemen.

105
00:05:31.957 --> 00:05:36.545
Welcome to the
Annual Underground Basketball Championship.

106
00:05:36.670 --> 00:05:38.255
Volleyball?

107
00:05:39.256 --> 00:05:41.591
Introducing the first teams of the day.

108
00:05:41.716 --> 00:05:47.973
Musculoso and Diggs
vs. the Ghost Pirate Twins!

109
00:05:48.098 --> 00:05:49.850
- Boo!
- Yeah. yeah.

110
00:05:49.975 --> 00:05:52.102
Let the game begin!

111
00:05:52.227 --> 00:05:56.022
All right. kid. Stay calm
and serve with grit and determination.

112
00:06:03.738 --> 00:06:06.867
And Musculoso and Diggs advance
to the next round!

113
00:06:06.992 --> 00:06:11.329
- It already is!
- Next up. Knights in a Medieval Joust!

114
00:06:15.333 --> 00:06:18.545
It's another win for Musculoso and Diggs!

115
00:06:18.670 --> 00:06:22.757
But will they be able to defeat
the humanoid robots?

116
00:06:22.883 --> 00:06:24.801
Fire ants?

117
00:06:24.926 --> 00:06:27.137
The Army of Bones?

118
00:06:27.262 --> 00:06:28.597
Yes. they can!

119
00:06:28.722 --> 00:06:32.976
It looks like Musculoso and Diggs
have made it to the top.

120
00:06:33.101 --> 00:06:34.644
It all comes to a head

121
00:06:34.769 --> 00:06:40.525
when Musculoso and Diggs
face off against Steve and Blake!

122
00:06:41.735 --> 00:06:43.862
I'm laughing at you all just to mock you.

123
00:06:43.987 --> 00:06:48.867
This game will be very dangerous
because it will be played on quicksand.

124
00:06:49.868 --> 00:06:50.869
That's disgusting.

125
00:06:50.994 --> 00:06:54.205
Don't worry. kid.
Keep moving.

126
00:06:55.206 --> 00:06:59.544
Try not to dwell too much
on how your girlfriend left you for Steve.

127
00:06:59.669 --> 00:07:02.130
I don't have a single thought in my head.

128
00:07:09.137 --> 00:07:10.597
Typical of Blake.

129
00:07:14.476 --> 00:07:16.019
What a hit!

130
00:07:16.144 --> 00:07:18.730
But unfortunately. that's out of the question.

131
00:07:18.855 --> 00:07:21.566
I don't know. Dan.
I think we're at a disadvantage.

132
00:07:21.691 --> 00:07:24.819
No. kid.
Remember why you're doing all this.

133
00:07:24.945 --> 00:07:26.154
Here. it's your turn to serve.

134
00:07:27.572 --> 00:07:28.823
By Starla.

135
00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:33.745
Steve and Blake score the first point!

136
00:07:40.877 --> 00:07:45.924
Steve and Blake are in the lead. Will
Musculoso and Diggs be able to make a comeback?

137
00:07:46.049 --> 00:07:48.009
Starla. you need to listen to me.

138
00:07:48.134 --> 00:07:52.347
Is there any other way I can prove
my worth? I'll do anything for you.

139
00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:56.643
For me? You should find
a purpose for yourself.

140
00:07:56.768 --> 00:07:59.354
- You still don't get it.
- No?

141
00:07:59.479 --> 00:08:00.939
Okay. we're back.

142
00:08:01.064 --> 00:08:03.858
Listen. kid.
I know it sounds discouraging. but...

143
00:08:03.984 --> 00:08:05.318
Are you okay?

144
00:08:05.443 --> 00:08:06.736
Pass me the ball.

145
00:08:06.861 --> 00:08:08.738
- I'm going to show you a purpose.
- What do you mean?

146
00:08:08.863 --> 00:08:11.908
I'm going to show you so much purpose
that you won't know what to do with it.

147
00:08:12.033 --> 00:08:14.327
Would you like a glass of water or...

148
00:08:14.452 --> 00:08:17.414
It's going to be like a tsunami—on purpose.

149
00:08:21.668 --> 00:08:25.964
And Musculoso scores
the second point for his team!

150
00:08:26.089 --> 00:08:27.382
- Wow!
- Again.

151
00:08:28.758 --> 00:08:29.884
What is my purpose?

152
00:08:31.177 --> 00:08:32.303
I don't know either!

153
00:08:34.514 --> 00:08:36.474
What is my purpose?

154
00:08:38.476 --> 00:08:40.520
The next point wins.

155
00:08:41.730 --> 00:08:44.357
All right. kid. This is it. Focus.

156
00:08:44.482 --> 00:08:47.944
How can I focus
if I don't know where I'm going in life?

157
00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:50.697
- Calm down. kid.
- What if I never find out?

158
00:08:50.822 --> 00:08:52.532
Remember what I said at the beginning.

159
00:08:52.657 --> 00:08:55.452
What if Starla never loves me again?

160
00:08:57.996 --> 00:09:01.458
It looks like the stallion buckled under the pressure.

161
00:09:01.583 --> 00:09:06.087
You should find
a purpose on your own.

162
00:09:06.212 --> 00:09:07.422
I have a hot bone!

163
00:09:07.547 --> 00:09:11.509
Serve with determination. with purpose.
purpose. purpose.

164
00:09:11.634 --> 00:09:12.635
That's it!

165
00:09:15.513 --> 00:09:18.892
Powerful serve on the short ball!

166
00:09:26.691 --> 00:09:30.987
And that's it! Musculoso and Diggs win the case!

167
00:09:31.112 --> 00:09:33.948
That's it! Yay!

168
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:36.785
I let you guys win this one.

169
00:09:36.910 --> 00:09:40.413
Oh. no. I'm drowning.
Stop translating and help me.

170
00:09:40.538 --> 00:09:43.333
Gargle. gasp. choke. choke.

171
00:09:43.458 --> 00:09:48.254
- Coffee. coffee. coffee. coffee. coffee?
- Yes. I speak the language of coffee.

172
00:09:50.381 --> 00:09:53.968
Here is your scholarship.
Full scholarship to Reino Alado University.

173
00:09:54.094 --> 00:09:55.678
Your future has wings!

174
00:09:55.804 --> 00:09:58.223
- Thank you.
- I'm proud of you. kid.

175
00:09:58.348 --> 00:10:00.225
Yeah. bro. Let's do it again.

176
00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:01.851
What? No. I'm a ghost.

177
00:10:01.976 --> 00:10:04.854
My soul literally left my body.
just as Steve said.

178
00:10:04.979 --> 00:10:06.773
Sorry. I thought I had understood.

179
00:10:07.774 --> 00:10:09.109
A ghost?

180
00:10:09.234 --> 00:10:12.946
Mitch? I'm sorry for being so harsh.

181
00:10:13.071 --> 00:10:15.740
I didn't understand what he meant at first.

182
00:10:15.865 --> 00:10:18.326
- But now I understand.
- You understand?

183
00:10:18.451 --> 00:10:21.538
Yes. I needed to find myself.
to look within

184
00:10:21.663 --> 00:10:24.332
and discover its fundamental purpose.

185
00:10:24.457 --> 00:10:25.708
It's volleyball.

186
00:10:25.834 --> 00:10:27.377
You really do understand.

187
00:10:27.502 --> 00:10:29.003
Janine!

188
00:10:31.506 --> 00:10:35.468
- Mitch. will you take me back?
- Yes. baby.

189
00:10:37.137 --> 00:10:38.638
MUSCULAR

190
00:10:38.763 --> 00:10:40.140
Anyway. because of Benson.

191
00:10:40.265 --> 00:10:43.601
Six weeks later.
I broke my wrist and lost my volleyball bag.

192
00:10:43.726 --> 00:10:44.727
But that's okay.

193
00:10:44.853 --> 00:10:47.397
I learned that my true
purpose was to work at the park.

194
00:10:47.522 --> 00:10:50.692
And that's worth a lot more than a
$100 volleyball bag.

195
00:10:50.817 --> 00:10:52.068
A hundred dollars?

196
00:10:52.193 --> 00:10:55.071
I felt bad for years because I thought
it was a complete journey.

197
00:10:55.196 --> 00:10:58.616
Yes. A full trip
from the airport to campus.
